Batting average is a commonly used metric in cricket to evaluate a batsman's performance, calculated as the total number of runs scored divided by the number of times a batsman is dismissed; 
A valid batting average typically implies a non-zero number of innings or matches played; 
Strike rate refers to the number of runs a batsman scores per 100 balls faced in the game; 
Wickets taken are a measure of a bowler's performance, representing the number of batsmen a bowler gets out.

sql:
SELECT AVG(batting_stat.strike_rate) AS avg_strike_rate
FROM batting_statistics AS batting_stat
WHERE batting_stat.runs_off_bat > 2000;
